OL,3,CGovernment will 'consider' scrapping
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap, minister says
OL,6,FThe PM said "I'm not surprised there's
OL,7,Fa real passion about this in the
OL,8,FLabour Party."
OL,10,FThe prime minister's spokesman said
OL,11,F"nothing is out of scope" of the new
OL,12,Ftaskforce, but insisted there was no
OL,13,Fchange in position on the cap.
OL,15,FMinisters have so far suggested the
OL,16,Fstate of the public finances means
OL,17,Fthey cannot afford to abolish the
OL,18,Fbenefit limit unless economic growth
OL,19,Fis secured first.
