OL,3,CGovernment will 'consider' scrapping
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap, minister says
OL,6,FThe cap was introduced by then-
OL,7,FConservative chancellor George Osborne
OL,8,Fin 2015 and restricts child welfare
OL,9,Fpayments to the first two children
OL,10,Fborn to most families.
OL,12,FSNP Westminster leader Stephen Flynn
OL,13,Furged Scottish Labour MPs to back the
OL,14,Fparty's amendment to remove the cap,
OL,15,Fwhich could be debated on Monday.
OL,17,FIt's understood to have the support of
OL,18,Fformer Labour leader and now
OL,19,FIndependent MP Jeremy Corbyn as well
OL,20,Fas the Green and Plaid Cymru MPs.
