OL,3,CGovernment will 'consider' scrapping
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap, minister says
OL,6,FWhether the amendment is ultimately
OL,7,Fvoted on is up to Commons Speaker, Sir
OL,8,FLindsay Hoyle.
OL,10,FMr Flynn said ahead of the debate:
OL,11,F"The two-child cap was the Tories
OL,12,Foperating at their worst, so scrapping
OL,13,Fthe cap would deliver on the promise
OL,14,Fmade to the public for real change."
OL,16,FThe debate comes after Labour MP Rosie
OL,17,FDuffield said in a Sunday newspaper
OL,18,Fthe two-child benefit cap amounts to
OL,19,F"social cleansing" and is an "anti-
OL,20,Ffeminist and unequal piece of
OL,21,Flegislation".
